WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:00.710 --> 00:00:03.370
Get moving right now, get moving right now

3
00:00:03.590 --> 00:00:06.460
Hoisting our flag high, we'll make it somehow

4
00:00:12.770 --> 00:00:15.500
Setting out all on our own to cross the endless sea,

5
00:00:15.500 --> 00:00:18.060
you know what we're searching for

6
00:00:18.860 --> 00:00:21.810
The worldwide enigma, treasures undiscovered

7
00:00:21.900 --> 00:00:23.940
Picking's ripe, so let's go explore

8
00:00:24.820 --> 00:00:27.960
We're all so excited, our hearts can't keep quiet

9
00:00:27.960 --> 00:00:29.710
Nothing left to do but press on

10
00:00:29.710 --> 00:00:35.590
Trailing after footprints left by the dreamers before us

11
00:00:36.420 --> 00:00:39.390
Stormy nights can try their best to sink us

12
00:00:39.390 --> 00:00:42.390
We'll sail on, if we just stick together

13
00:00:42.390 --> 00:00:46.540
Try and stop us if you can

14
00:00:46.680 --> 00:00:47.860
We always pull through

15
00:00:48.760 --> 00:00:51.590
Get moving right now, get moving right now

16
00:00:51.720 --> 00:00:54.550
Hoisting our flag high, we'll make it somehow

17
00:00:54.600 --> 00:00:57.140
Even if we sometimes shed tears,

18
00:00:57.230 --> 00:01:00.580
and want to hide them from prying eyes

19
00:01:00.770 --> 00:01:03.520
But go and chase it, yeah, go and chase it

20
00:01:03.690 --> 00:01:06.520
Run the direction the compass points in

21
00:01:06.610 --> 00:01:09.230
All our dreams are straight ahead it says

22
00:01:09.230 --> 00:01:11.400
So don't sit back, let's chase it

23
00:01:18.830 --> 00:01:21.490
Get moving right now, get moving right now

24
00:01:21.800 --> 00:01:24.540
We have to pull through ahead of them all

25
00:01:24.630 --> 00:01:27.120
If we hold firm and stand our ground,

26
00:01:27.220 --> 00:01:30.540
I know the future's within our grasp

27
00:01:30.600 --> 00:01:33.630
So go and chase it, yeah, go and chase it

28
00:01:33.680 --> 00:01:36.510
The world's our oyster, it's waiting for us

29
00:01:36.560 --> 00:01:38.930
All the sadness and the joy we see,

30
00:01:39.150 --> 00:01:41.430
let's etch it in our hearts

31
00:01:50.090 --> 00:01:54.840
<b>Gear Second</b>

32
00:01:55.510 --> 00:01:58.640
Gear? Your techniques evolve?

33
00:01:58.640 --> 00:02:03.850
Are you giving off steam
to pretend you're a steam engine?

34
00:02:03.850 --> 00:02:05.520
What kind of a bluff is that?

35
00:02:10.320 --> 00:02:14.200
I'm glad I met you guys here.

36
00:02:15.660 --> 00:02:18.120
Gum-Gum...

37
00:02:21.410 --> 00:02:25.250
Are you trying to aim?
You're just giving me time to dodge.

38
00:02:27.840 --> 00:02:29.960
Try and hit me if you can.

39
00:02:29.960 --> 00:02:30.420
Shave!

40
00:02:30.420 --> 00:02:32.420
...Jet Pistol!

41
00:02:43.980 --> 00:02:44.980
Rifle!

42
00:02:54.990 --> 00:02:56.740
I can't even see him!

43
00:03:01.080 --> 00:03:02.330
Stamp!

44
00:03:03.450 --> 00:03:03.960
And...

45
00:03:03.960 --> 00:03:05.160
Spear!

46
00:03:07.420 --> 00:03:08.670
Missile!

47
00:03:19.180 --> 00:03:20.300
No way...!

48
00:03:25.140 --> 00:03:27.190
No, there's no doubt.

49
00:03:27.850 --> 00:03:31.190
I'm glad I met you guys here.

50
00:03:31.730 --> 00:03:38.280
This boy has mastered shave,
one of the Six Powers!

51
00:03:39.910 --> 00:03:40.700
Air Door!

52
00:03:47.420 --> 00:03:48.540
He disappeared...

53
00:03:52.380 --> 00:03:54.630
This is ridiculous!

54
00:03:54.630 --> 00:03:56.550
He got strong...

55
00:03:56.550 --> 00:04:01.470
Strong enough to use it
and to do so with ease.

56
00:04:01.970 --> 00:04:07.310
But... there's no way someone could be
faster than a Six Powers master!

57
00:04:07.310 --> 00:04:09.100
A Six Powers master cannot lose!

58
00:04:11.560 --> 00:04:16.780
Turning his body into a door
ought to restrain his movements.

59
00:04:16.780 --> 00:04:20.160
I'll go all in and settle this in an instant.

60
00:04:22.530 --> 00:04:23.620
Door Door!

61
00:04:29.670 --> 00:04:32.380
I saw how you guys move when you vanish.

62
00:04:32.880 --> 00:04:36.880
You kick the ground dozens of times a second.

63
00:04:37.510 --> 00:04:39.010
I got the hang of it too.

64
00:04:39.010 --> 00:04:42.180
I just needed to learn how to do it.

65
00:04:43.100 --> 00:04:45.930
Gum-Gum...

66
00:04:46.850 --> 00:04:49.850
I will meet it head-on...
with the strongest iron body technique!

67
00:04:51.980 --> 00:04:53.860
Iron Body: Adamantine!

68
00:04:53.860 --> 00:04:56.110
...Jet Bazooka!

69
00:05:10.870 --> 00:05:13.130
You sure are tough.

70
00:05:15.000 --> 00:05:18.970
Fine, I'll show you something even better.

71
00:05:18.970 --> 00:05:20.510
Watch this!

72
00:05:23.680 --> 00:05:24.850
Gear...

73
00:05:37.900 --> 00:05:39.360
I'm beat!

74
00:05:40.030 --> 00:05:42.740
I guess my body still can't keep up.

75
00:05:44.820 --> 00:05:48.040
Well, I can't worry about my body now.

76
00:05:49.620 --> 00:05:51.830
I lost a lot of time.

77
00:05:51.870 --> 00:05:55.790
<b>Courthouse</b>

78
00:05:51.870 --> 00:05:54.250
<b>Gates of Justice</b>

79
00:05:51.870 --> 00:05:56.870
<b>Tower of Justice</b>

80
00:05:53.450 --> 00:05:57.960
<b>Island Gate</b>

81
00:05:55.790 --> 00:05:57.960
<b>Courthouse</b>

82
00:05:57.960 --> 00:06:00.010
Dammit! What's going on?!

83
00:06:00.010 --> 00:06:02.220
Cannons! Fire the cannons!

84
00:06:02.220 --> 00:06:04.140
We'll be crushed!

85
00:06:05.510 --> 00:06:09.140
That's useless! Those things
won't stop us, you half-pints!

86
00:06:09.140 --> 00:06:13.060
You won't stop Oimo, either!

87
00:06:16.020 --> 00:06:18.150
You're kidding me!

88
00:06:18.480 --> 00:06:21.570
I can't believe these two
gatekeeper lugs are on our side now!

89
00:06:22.950 --> 00:06:25.450
It's thanks to the bond between warriors!

90
00:06:25.450 --> 00:06:27.280
Now, my brothers!

91
00:06:27.280 --> 00:06:29.660
We're almost at the courthouse!

92
00:06:29.660 --> 00:06:31.160
Forward!

93
00:06:31.160 --> 00:06:34.160
<b>Island Gate</b>
<b>Tower of Justice</b>

94
00:06:31.910 --> 00:06:34.160
<b>Courthouse</b>

95
00:06:32.660 --> 00:06:35.540
What're you doing?!
Hurry up and go in!

96
00:06:35.540 --> 00:06:38.420
The pirates are inside
the courthouse, aren't they?!

97
00:06:38.420 --> 00:06:43.050
Yeah, but a frog at the main door
is keeping us out!

98
00:06:43.050 --> 00:06:44.630
A frog?!

99
00:06:46.430 --> 00:06:49.720
Don't let anyone in, Yokozuna! Stand tall!

100
00:06:50.100 --> 00:06:53.600
If our defenses fall, thousands of guards
are gonna flood the place!

101
00:06:53.600 --> 00:06:55.600
Hold out till the drawbridge drops!

102
00:06:59.190 --> 00:07:01.530
<b>Courthouse Right Tower</b>

103
00:07:02.940 --> 00:07:05.200
We only need one of us to bust through!

104
00:07:05.200 --> 00:07:09.450
No matter what it takes, we're gonna
pull that lever and drop the drawbridge!

105
00:07:11.570 --> 00:07:13.870
<b>Courthouse Left Tower</b>

106
00:07:19.960 --> 00:07:21.300
Big Sis Mozu!

107
00:07:21.960 --> 00:07:23.170
I'm fine! Get going!

108
00:07:23.550 --> 00:07:27.890
Lower that damn bridge and get
the Straw Hats to the Tower of Justice!

109
00:07:28.390 --> 00:07:30.720
Stop them! Don't you dare let them through!

110
00:07:30.720 --> 00:07:32.600
Out of the way!

111
00:07:37.940 --> 00:07:43.110
Why did that swordsman
and his comrades head upstairs earlier?

112
00:07:45.740 --> 00:07:47.700
Like I'd tell you anything!

113
00:07:47.700 --> 00:07:48.820
What?!

114
00:07:48.820 --> 00:07:52.790
But I hope for your sake
that Big Bro Franky is okay!

115
00:07:53.320 --> 00:07:55.450
<b>Courthouse Courtroom</b>

116
00:07:55.830 --> 00:07:58.750
Meet them head on! Bring down those pirates!

117
00:07:58.750 --> 00:08:02.340
Damn guards! I didn't realize
so many were still inside!

118
00:08:04.710 --> 00:08:06.380
There they are! Take them down!

119
00:08:06.380 --> 00:08:08.010
Out of our way!

120
00:08:08.840 --> 00:08:12.220
Hey! Watch where
you're hurling them, Chopper!

121
00:08:14.270 --> 00:08:19.100
Guilty! Guilty! Guilty! Guilty! Guilty!

122
00:08:16.600 --> 00:08:19.100
Guilty! Guilty! Guilty!

123
00:08:19.100 --> 00:08:22.270
Just what the hell are you?!

124
00:08:22.270 --> 00:08:24.230
Actually, where the hell am I?!

125
00:08:25.270 --> 00:08:27.400
<b>Tower of Justice</b>

126
00:08:33.530 --> 00:08:36.700
We're taking Franky and Nico Robin
to the Gates of Justice already?

127
00:08:36.700 --> 00:08:38.960
That's right! Just do what I say!

128
00:08:38.960 --> 00:08:42.330
But the escort ship departing
from the Gates of Justice isn't ready!

129
00:08:42.330 --> 00:08:46.460
That's fine! We'll just wait for it
on the other side of the gates!

130
00:08:46.460 --> 00:08:50.430
The idea is to deprive
the pirates of their objective.

131
00:08:50.430 --> 00:08:54.890
Once we're through the Gates of Justice,
they won't be able to interfere anymore!

132
00:08:55.470 --> 00:08:59.230
Also, gather all the members of CP9!

133
00:08:59.230 --> 00:09:00.390
– Yes, sir!
– Yes, sir!

134
00:09:04.400 --> 00:09:05.610
Okay, then…

135
00:09:06.150 --> 00:09:08.030
Stand up, you two!

136
00:09:08.030 --> 00:09:10.610
Your journey to hell starts now.

137
00:09:10.610 --> 00:09:13.660
After that, we'll just hunt down
each pirate at our leisure.

138
00:09:18.410 --> 00:09:21.370
Everything these guys do is something else.

139
00:09:21.370 --> 00:09:25.000
Anyone with common sense
would steer clear of this place.

140
00:09:25.840 --> 00:09:27.630
Just wait and see, Chimney.

141
00:09:28.170 --> 00:09:35.510
Whether they live or die,
they did what no one could for centuries.

142
00:09:35.510 --> 00:09:38.970
The whole world will be shocked
by what happened here.

143
00:09:40.140 --> 00:09:47.650
When the dust settles on this battlefield,
the entire world will know that straw hat kid.

144
00:09:54.620 --> 00:09:59.620
Robin!

145
00:10:01.120 --> 00:10:01.960
He's here!

146
00:10:03.960 --> 00:10:05.130
Luffy...

147
00:10:05.130 --> 00:10:09.590
We've come to get you!

148
00:10:10.760 --> 00:10:15.850
Chief! A guy in a straw hat is shouting
something on the courthouse rooftop!

149
00:10:16.220 --> 00:10:19.680
I think it's Straw Hat Luffy,
the captain of the Straw Hat Pirates!

150
00:10:19.680 --> 00:10:23.980
Don't be ridiculous! When I checked earlier,
Blueno was on the roof!

151
00:10:24.560 --> 00:10:27.110
Wasn't he standing watch?! That idiot!

152
00:10:27.110 --> 00:10:29.070
What's he doing at a time like this?!

153
00:10:35.110 --> 00:10:37.530
Must be from all the fighting...

154
00:10:38.990 --> 00:10:40.120
I'm starving!

155
00:10:41.080 --> 00:10:44.170
This is the perfect time for...

156
00:10:45.420 --> 00:10:47.670
lunch!

157
00:10:49.750 --> 00:10:54.090
Good thing I put 'em in my pockets!

158
00:10:54.630 --> 00:10:55.760
So good!

159
00:11:02.680 --> 00:11:06.060
So that's him? Straw Hat Luffy...

160
00:11:06.060 --> 00:11:07.940
What the hell is going on?

161
00:11:08.690 --> 00:11:11.030
What's Blueno doin–

162
00:11:13.940 --> 00:11:15.450
Impossible...

163
00:11:15.450 --> 00:11:17.910
He couldn't have...

164
00:11:18.280 --> 00:11:22.750
He's a member of CP9—
a Six Powers master with devil fruit abilities...

165
00:11:22.750 --> 00:11:26.210
Blueno, a superhuman
whose power level exceeds 800!

166
00:11:28.210 --> 00:11:30.130
Alright! I'm all better!

167
00:11:30.500 --> 00:11:33.880
He lost to a brat... like him?

168
00:11:39.970 --> 00:11:42.260
Ch-Chief! What should we do?!

169
00:11:42.260 --> 00:11:45.180
Lucci... Where's Lucci?

170
00:11:46.230 --> 00:11:49.100
Call in Lucci and the others!
Gather everyone here!

171
00:11:49.650 --> 00:11:55.190
As the chief of CP9, I'll order them
to annihilate Straw Hat Luffy and his crew!

172
00:11:55.190 --> 00:11:56.820
Notify the Baskervilles, too!

173
00:11:56.820 --> 00:11:59.990
Tell them that if the pirates
somehow lower the drawbridge,

174
00:11:59.990 --> 00:12:02.410
all three of their heads will roll!

175
00:12:02.410 --> 00:12:03.490
– Yes, sir!
– Yes, sir!

176
00:12:07.210 --> 00:12:09.670
Keep your chin up, Nico Robin.

177
00:12:11.340 --> 00:12:15.630
They've already come this far.

178
00:12:15.630 --> 00:12:18.300
Y'know, it's pretty wild.

179
00:12:19.050 --> 00:12:24.930
I get that you accepted the government's
terms of surrender to save your friends,

180
00:12:24.930 --> 00:12:30.270
but you saw how casually that
dumbass chief reneged on your deal.

181
00:12:30.810 --> 00:12:36.320
Quietly giving in and surrendering
isn't gonna save anyone.

182
00:12:36.320 --> 00:12:41.370
At this point, your only option is
to accept their help and escape with them.

183
00:12:41.870 --> 00:12:45.870
Yet... you're looking pretty glum over there.

184
00:12:45.870 --> 00:12:50.870
It's like you're still running around,
trying to find a way out on your own.

185
00:12:52.330 --> 00:12:55.960
Are you afraid your friends
are gonna die here?

186
00:12:55.960 --> 00:12:59.930
If you keep avoiding them,
they can't save you.

187
00:12:59.930 --> 00:13:01.430
Hello?!

188
00:13:01.430 --> 00:13:03.930
Is anyone there?!

189
00:13:08.350 --> 00:13:11.310
I'll help you see Straw Hat right now.

190
00:13:11.770 --> 00:13:12.600
What?!

191
00:13:14.150 --> 00:13:15.860
Listen up!

192
00:13:16.230 --> 00:13:19.110
We've got to hurry and get
Nico Robin away from Straw Hat!

193
00:13:19.110 --> 00:13:21.240
We're departing for the Gates of Justice!

194
00:13:21.240 --> 00:13:22.820
Bring those two!

195
00:13:22.820 --> 00:13:24.410
Ch-Chief!

196
00:13:24.780 --> 00:13:26.370
Just hurry up and do it!

197
00:13:26.990 --> 00:13:28.660
But...

198
00:13:28.660 --> 00:13:31.670
Franky's butt is inflating!

199
00:13:32.620 --> 00:13:33.830
What the hell is that?!

200
00:13:35.210 --> 00:13:37.050
Oh, Spanda!

201
00:13:37.050 --> 00:13:41.720
Being well aware of my impending demise,
I've chosen the path of self-destruction.

202
00:13:41.720 --> 00:13:42.720
What?!

203
00:13:42.720 --> 00:13:46.350
At the very least, you vile scum
will go down with me.

204
00:13:46.350 --> 00:13:48.470
Just... Just wait, you idiot!

205
00:13:48.890 --> 00:13:55.520
By way of this three-kilometer-wide explosion,
my life will end here. Do not stop me.

206
00:13:56.440 --> 00:13:59.400
Don't do it! Help! Don't take me with you!

207
00:14:00.860 --> 00:14:02.360
Three...

208
00:14:02.360 --> 00:14:03.360
Two...

209
00:14:03.360 --> 00:14:05.490
Dammit! I can't die here!

210
00:14:06.030 --> 00:14:07.530
One...

211
00:14:07.530 --> 00:14:09.500
Stop it!

212
00:14:11.790 --> 00:14:13.330
Let's go, Nico Robin!

213
00:14:16.250 --> 00:14:18.880
Coup de Boo!

214
00:14:24.220 --> 00:14:27.220
All right! It broke the chains, too.

215
00:14:27.220 --> 00:14:29.220
Wh-Wh-Whoa! We're gonna fall!

216
00:14:31.930 --> 00:14:33.350
Super!

217
00:14:45.410 --> 00:14:47.410
That was close.

218
00:14:47.410 --> 00:14:50.120
Good thing there was a fence.

219
00:14:51.370 --> 00:14:53.250
Hey, you aren't hurt, are you?

220
00:14:58.090 --> 00:15:03.630
If I had another bottle of cola, I could've
gotten us to the other side with a Coup de Vent.

221
00:15:03.970 --> 00:15:04.970
Oh, well.

222
00:15:04.970 --> 00:15:07.090
There's Straw Hat.

223
00:15:07.090 --> 00:15:09.760
Now, give him your answer.

224
00:15:10.470 --> 00:15:11.470
He tricked us!

225
00:15:11.470 --> 00:15:16.440
Chief! Franky and Nico Robin broke
their chains and made it to the balcony!

226
00:15:16.440 --> 00:15:19.440
You fools! What are you doing?!
Capture them already!

227
00:15:19.440 --> 00:15:21.820
If you let them escape, I'll have you all hanged!

228
00:15:21.820 --> 00:15:22.940
– What?!
– What?!

229
00:15:31.370 --> 00:15:33.950
Hey! Robin!

230
00:15:33.950 --> 00:15:36.330
What a relief! You're still here!

231
00:15:38.330 --> 00:15:39.540
Luffy...

232
00:15:39.540 --> 00:15:41.960
Capture them again no matter what!

233
00:15:41.960 --> 00:15:43.920
Get lost, punks!

234
00:15:43.920 --> 00:15:46.430
Weapons Left!

235
00:15:49.390 --> 00:15:51.390
Looks like Franky's there too.

236
00:15:51.390 --> 00:15:53.850
Alright! Just wait right there!

237
00:15:55.180 --> 00:15:57.100
It's far, but I'll try to fly over!

238
00:16:03.320 --> 00:16:05.740
Gum-Gum...

239
00:16:05.740 --> 00:16:07.150
Wait!

240
00:16:13.240 --> 00:16:15.040
How many times do I have to tell you?!

241
00:16:15.790 --> 00:16:19.670
I'm never rejoining your crew!

242
00:16:19.670 --> 00:16:20.880
Go away!

243
00:16:20.880 --> 00:16:23.840
I never want to see your faces again!

244
00:16:24.300 --> 00:16:26.170
Why are you trying to save me?!

245
00:16:27.090 --> 00:16:29.180
Why are you trying to save me?!

246
00:16:29.510 --> 00:16:32.890
I didn't want this.

247
00:16:34.100 --> 00:16:37.560
When did I ever ask you to do this?!

248
00:16:44.730 --> 00:16:46.610
I just...

249
00:16:46.610 --> 00:16:50.360
want to die!

250
00:16:54.410 --> 00:16:56.910
Hilarious! What the heck are they doing?!

251
00:16:58.620 --> 00:17:00.500
What the hell is your problem?!

252
00:17:00.500 --> 00:17:03.170
Those guys risked
life and limb to come get you!

253
00:17:03.170 --> 00:17:04.000
But you–

254
00:17:04.000 --> 00:17:05.590
That was their own choice.

255
00:17:05.590 --> 00:17:06.760
What?!

256
00:17:06.760 --> 00:17:07.460
Don't be ridic–

257
00:17:12.090 --> 00:17:13.140
You're in our way.

258
00:17:15.720 --> 00:17:18.480
Blowing off some steam, Kaku?!

259
00:17:18.480 --> 00:17:20.940
Is it because you ate such a weird fruit?

260
00:17:21.900 --> 00:17:23.400
Shut your trap!

261
00:17:23.400 --> 00:17:24.650
My fruit is nifty!

262
00:17:28.650 --> 00:17:31.530
Oh? Are we just facing Straw Hat?

263
00:17:33.410 --> 00:17:39.250
Even if he is alone, it is indeed
an impressive feat to have made it this far.

264
00:17:42.710 --> 00:17:45.460
No kidding. The guy took out Blueno!

265
00:17:46.460 --> 00:17:48.050
How crazy is that?!

266
00:17:48.050 --> 00:17:52.090
I guess he lost his edge
after running a bar for five years, huh?

267
00:17:52.090 --> 00:17:54.970
He got so rusty that he lost?

268
00:17:54.970 --> 00:17:56.970
He went down hard.

269
00:18:00.640 --> 00:18:03.690
All right! I'm glad that you're here, CP9!

270
00:18:03.690 --> 00:18:05.360
But wait a little longer.

271
00:18:05.360 --> 00:18:08.940
The Straw Hats have just started imploding!

272
00:18:08.940 --> 00:18:10.610
How could we not watch this?!

273
00:18:11.610 --> 00:18:13.320
It's prime entertainment!

274
00:18:24.920 --> 00:18:27.630
Good job, Yokozuna! Keep it up!

275
00:18:36.350 --> 00:18:37.220
Guilty...

276
00:18:37.220 --> 00:18:39.180
Guilty!

277
00:18:40.140 --> 00:18:41.890
It's the Guilty Jurors!

278
00:18:41.890 --> 00:18:43.270
Step aside.

279
00:18:43.270 --> 00:18:46.100
We'll pass down the verdict
for that frog's crime.

280
00:18:53.820 --> 00:18:55.240
Guilty...

281
00:18:55.240 --> 00:18:56.110
Guilty!

282
00:19:10.840 --> 00:19:12.010
Seriously!

283
00:19:12.010 --> 00:19:14.130
What the heck are these guys?!

284
00:19:14.130 --> 00:19:16.510
Guilty! Guilty!

285
00:19:16.930 --> 00:19:18.010
Let's go, Chopper!

286
00:19:18.010 --> 00:19:20.260
No, I mean, go, Chopper!

287
00:19:20.260 --> 00:19:22.220
Wh-What?! Just me?!

288
00:19:23.390 --> 00:19:28.730
I never imagined this island
even had a chief justice.

289
00:19:29.190 --> 00:19:33.820
I thought everyone taken to Enies Lobby
was already considered guilty.

290
00:19:33.820 --> 00:19:38.160
I'd heard they just came here to pass
through an empty courthouse.

291
00:19:38.160 --> 00:19:41.410
You pirates couldn't be more wrong.

292
00:19:41.410 --> 00:19:45.710
This is the most authoritative,
just court in the world.

293
00:19:45.710 --> 00:19:48.170
We conduct fair trials!

294
00:19:48.540 --> 00:19:49.670
However...

295
00:19:49.670 --> 00:19:53.760
...the jurors who issue verdicts
of guilty or not guilty...

296
00:19:53.760 --> 00:19:56.130
are former pirates on death row...

297
00:19:56.130 --> 00:20:00.050
who wish to take you down with them!

298
00:20:00.050 --> 00:20:04.020
Tattoo: "Guilty"

299
00:20:04.520 --> 00:20:06.770
Judged by death-row convicts?!

300
00:20:06.770 --> 00:20:09.600
Hence, no one in this town...

301
00:20:09.600 --> 00:20:10.730
No one!

302
00:20:10.730 --> 00:20:13.980
...has ever been found not guilty.

303
00:20:13.980 --> 00:20:15.320
Kiwi!

304
00:20:19.490 --> 00:20:20.410
Guys!

305
00:20:21.580 --> 00:20:23.030
Guilty!

306
00:20:24.080 --> 00:20:25.330
Guilty!

307
00:20:26.040 --> 00:20:27.750
Dammit! They're...

308
00:20:27.750 --> 00:20:29.330
Stand tall!

309
00:20:29.670 --> 00:20:33.090
If we don't get through here,
then we ain't bringing down the drawbridge!

310
00:20:33.090 --> 00:20:35.880
We left Bro's rescue to Straw Hat!

311
00:20:35.880 --> 00:20:40.220
We can't be the ones holding them up here!

312
00:20:44.010 --> 00:20:45.600
Yokozuna!

313
00:20:47.480 --> 00:20:51.480
I can't believe you took
all those big iron balls to the face!

314
00:20:51.860 --> 00:20:53.900
You bastards!

315
00:20:55.650 --> 00:20:56.650
You should give up!

316
00:20:56.650 --> 00:20:58.530
We've still got over 6,000 men!

317
00:20:58.530 --> 00:21:00.910
All right, everyone into the courthouse!

318
00:21:01.410 --> 00:21:04.030
Crush the pirates!

319
00:21:19.880 --> 00:21:21.590
Wh-What's going on?

320
00:21:21.590 --> 00:21:23.090
Why are the giants...?

321
00:21:23.090 --> 00:21:24.220
Frog!

322
00:21:25.600 --> 00:21:27.140
H-Hey!

323
00:21:27.140 --> 00:21:28.930
Tell me what's going on!

324
00:21:30.310 --> 00:21:32.770
You're with Mr. Straw Hat.

325
00:21:32.770 --> 00:21:34.650
What the heck is going on?!

326
00:21:35.440 --> 00:21:38.990
Look how many guards he's been holding back!

327
00:21:38.990 --> 00:21:41.530
Yeah! That frog is something else!

328
00:21:51.370 --> 00:21:52.870
Where the hell are they?

329
00:21:52.870 --> 00:21:55.090
They ran off again.

330
00:21:55.090 --> 00:21:56.960
We don't have time for this.

331
00:21:59.210 --> 00:22:00.340
Oh, yeah...

332
00:22:00.340 --> 00:22:03.130
It doesn't matter as long as
I keep heading up, right?

333
00:22:03.470 --> 00:22:04.800
Dragon Twister!

334
00:22:08.060 --> 00:22:09.810
Wait! What?!

335
00:22:16.440 --> 00:22:18.280
It's dangerous here, too!

336
00:22:30.830 --> 00:22:33.960
You guys really are incredible!

337
00:22:33.960 --> 00:22:36.380
You somehow tamed those giants.

338
00:22:36.380 --> 00:22:38.300
You're a pretty scary guy!

339
00:22:38.300 --> 00:22:39.670
Huh? Er... Well...

340
00:22:40.920 --> 00:22:41.970
Oh, right!

341
00:22:41.970 --> 00:22:44.510
All your friends are headed to the rooftop.

342
00:22:44.510 --> 00:22:45.260
The rooftop?

343
00:22:45.260 --> 00:22:46.340
You need to go too!

344
00:22:46.680 --> 00:22:49.640
Leave it to me, King of Snipers.

345
00:22:50.310 --> 00:22:51.640
Huh?

346
00:22:56.690 --> 00:22:57.940
You wanna die?!

347
00:22:58.940 --> 00:23:00.070
That's right!

348
00:23:04.650 --> 00:23:06.160
Hey, Chief.

349
00:23:06.160 --> 00:23:09.990
If we just hop over there and take out
that one guy, all this'll be over, right?

350
00:23:09.990 --> 00:23:11.700
Let's just wait.

351
00:23:11.700 --> 00:23:18.590
The captain comes all this way to rescue his crewmate
just to have her ultimately refuse his help.

352
00:23:20.090 --> 00:23:24.380
Have you ever seen something
as comical as that?

353
00:23:24.880 --> 00:23:26.510
Robin!

354
00:23:26.510 --> 00:23:28.350
You wanna die?!

355
00:23:30.510 --> 00:23:32.140
Listen to his pathetic shout!

356
00:23:32.140 --> 00:23:34.060
I can only imagine the look on his...

357
00:23:35.810 --> 00:23:38.360
What the heck are you talking about?

358
00:23:38.360 --> 00:23:40.360
Wh-Wh-What?!

359
00:23:40.360 --> 00:23:42.190
H-He's picking his nose!

360
00:23:44.490 --> 00:23:46.360
Listen, Robin.

361
00:23:46.360 --> 00:23:49.740
We've already come this far, so...

362
00:24:00.090 --> 00:24:01.960
we're gonna rescue you anyway.

363
00:24:01.960 --> 00:24:02.710
Landed!

364
00:24:05.840 --> 00:24:09.260
If you still wanna die after that,

365
00:24:09.260 --> 00:24:11.640
that's your business.

366
00:24:15.390 --> 00:24:17.560
Ow, ow, ow...

367
00:24:17.560 --> 00:24:19.690
Are you okay, Chopper?

368
00:24:19.690 --> 00:24:21.270
Yeah, I'm all right.

369
00:24:21.940 --> 00:24:24.440
But what just happened?

370
00:24:25.070 --> 00:24:27.030
I have a hunch.

371
00:24:36.790 --> 00:24:39.330
I should've come up here
like this from the start.

372
00:24:39.330 --> 00:24:40.380
Zoro!

373
00:24:40.710 --> 00:24:41.840
So it really was you!

374
00:24:41.840 --> 00:24:43.710
You're lucky we're alive!

375
00:24:43.710 --> 00:24:47.050
If we had been right in the middle
of it, we would've died!

376
00:24:47.050 --> 00:24:48.930
Huh? Did something happen to you guys?

377
00:24:49.510 --> 00:24:51.050
Take that!

378
00:24:51.050 --> 00:24:52.140
Dash!

379
00:24:52.140 --> 00:24:54.390
Boar Stew Shoot!

380
00:24:57.020 --> 00:24:59.270
I am, of course, the first to arrive.

381
00:24:59.270 --> 00:25:01.270
Now, I've kept Robin waiting.

382
00:25:01.270 --> 00:25:02.690
I'm coming to rescue–

383
00:25:02.690 --> 00:25:04.070
Moss!

384
00:25:04.070 --> 00:25:07.190
Moss Head! How did you get here before me?!

385
00:25:07.190 --> 00:25:10.070
Oh? What took you so long?
Did you get lost?

386
00:25:10.070 --> 00:25:13.200
H-H-Hey, hey, hey now, hey!

387
00:25:13.200 --> 00:25:16.120
Don't go stealing my line!

388
00:25:19.460 --> 00:25:21.670
Sogeking!

389
00:25:26.670 --> 00:25:28.340
What?! He's flying!

390
00:25:28.340 --> 00:25:30.340
Amazing!

391
00:25:30.340 --> 00:25:32.430
Where's he been all this time?

392
00:25:38.020 --> 00:25:40.520
Is he... gonna land okay?

393
00:25:44.810 --> 00:25:46.980
Whoa… one after another…

394
00:25:48.230 --> 00:25:50.490
At any rate...

395
00:25:51.570 --> 00:25:52.860
Sogeking!

396
00:25:52.860 --> 00:25:55.740
...they did march straight into headquarters.

397
00:25:55.740 --> 00:26:00.370
Though they may be our enemy, their resolve is admirable!

398
00:26:02.790 --> 00:26:06.090
Th-Th-There's that many pirates?!

399
00:26:26.860 --> 00:26:29.110
Just hear me out, Robin!

400
00:26:29.110 --> 00:26:34.160
You can go ahead and say you wanna die
or whatever, but say those things...

401
00:26:34.740 --> 00:26:36.160
by our side!

402
00:26:38.580 --> 00:26:40.290
He's right, Robin my love!

403
00:26:40.290 --> 00:26:42.540
Robin! Come back!

404
00:27:03.850 --> 00:27:06.230
Hey, Sogeking. Can you stand up?

405
00:27:06.230 --> 00:27:07.020
Huh...?

406
00:27:07.940 --> 00:27:09.110
Naturally.

407
00:27:09.730 --> 00:27:12.110
'Tis but a scratch!

408
00:27:18.950 --> 00:27:21.120
Don't worry. I'm all right.

409
00:28:04.120 --> 00:28:06.250
Just leave the rest to us!

410
00:28:12.220 --> 00:28:18.760
I know there’s something that I need to say,

411
00:28:19.140 --> 00:28:22.730
but I can’t seem to find the words

412
00:28:22.980 --> 00:28:30.610
Wandering aimlessly, forever on the hunt, that’s how I’ve lived

413
00:28:30.610 --> 00:28:36.370
And now there’s something right in front of me,

414
00:28:37.570 --> 00:28:41.080
a light that shines brighter than gold

415
00:28:41.450 --> 00:28:46.460
But as I trail behind, it speeds out of sight.

416
00:28:46.460 --> 00:28:53.050
What’s going on? Scared of what’s yet to come

417
00:28:53.380 --> 00:28:59.300
So many times, so many times as we both stumbled on the way

418
00:28:59.510 --> 00:29:02.310
We’ve had our highs, we’ve had our lows;

419
00:29:02.600 --> 00:29:05.390
Yeah, we just take it day by day

420
00:29:05.690 --> 00:29:11.940
Never forget that even when the night snuffs out the light

421
00:29:12.230 --> 00:29:18.570
When the dark has passed the sun will rise again
